Wonk is a Hispanic slang word meaning "to masturbate". It was coined by Spanish expatriot and television personality [[Guy Saldaña]] during an extended expulsion to the United States, where, faced with masturbatory situations in his show [[Pasión Salvaje]], he attempted to describe it with the British term [[wank]]. However, his poor knowledge of the English language caused him to mistakenly pronounce it as "wonk", the form in which it has been popularized. It has since become a household term for Hispanics, a more polite alternative to ruder Spanish terms such as [[hacerse una paja]] and the more clinical [[masturbarse]]. His mispronounciation, left uncorrected by his English speaking fans who assumed it was intentionally humorous, was extended to the even ruder "teetwonk", again a misinterpretation of the British term [[titwank]]. This, of course, is a reference to the sexual practice of sliding the male member through the breasts of a female for pleasure. The usage is largely self explanatory, identical to [[wank]].
